        "body": "You apply your makeup perfectly in the bathroom, put on a shirt that makes you look vibrant in the mirror, and step outside. Out of nowhere, you catch your reflection in a store window, and you look completely different. Your foundation is heavily mismatched, your shirt looks dull, and your skin looks flushed or sallow. You are a victim of Metamerism—the scientific phenomenon where lighting dictates color. Understanding how lighting alters your skin tone is the most critical factor in looking consistently flawless, whether you are in an office, on a date, or taking photos for Instagram."
