        "body": "Have you ever bought an outfit that looked phenomenal in the store dressing room, only to walk outside and realize it looks completely different—and worse—in the sun? The drastic shift between how clothing looks under the sun compared to indoor lighting isn't a trick of your mind; it is a hardline rule of optical physics known as Color Rendering Index (CRI) and Spectral Power Distribution. Understanding this difference is essential for shopping smart and matching clothes to your skin tone accurately."
