        "body": "You spend thirty minutes perfectly blending your foundation, contour, and eyeshadow in your bathroom mirror. You look flawless. But the moment you sit down in your office under the harsh fluorescent lights, or step outside into the glaring sun to take a selfie, your face looks completely different. Your foundation suddenly looks orange, your contour looks muddy, and your entire face looks slightly exhausted. You haven't lost your makeup skills. You have fallen victim to Metamerism—the scientific phenomenon where lighting dictates color perception. Because makeup is fundamentally built on colored pigments, the lighting in the room actively changes the chemical appearance of those pigments. Here is exactly how lighting destroys your makeup, and how to outsmart it."
