        "heading": "Introduction",
        "body": "The Color Wheel is the singular most important tool in the history of visual design. Invented by Sir Isaac Newton in 1666, it maps the entire visible light spectrum into a circular, logical arrangement that reveals the hidden mathematical relationships between every color in existence. In the world of fashion, the Color Wheel is your ultimate cheat sheet. It eliminates the subjective guesswork of \"does this match?\" and replaces it with objective, physics-based rules. Here is exactly how the Color Wheel works and how you can leverage it to permanently upgrade your wardrobe."
